Here is a JavaScript function that uses regular expressions to extract a three character code like "1Jn" from a filename in format "57-1Jn.usfm":

```javascript
function getCode(filename) {
  const regex = /(\d+)-([A-Za-z0-9]{3})\.usfm/;
  const match = filename.match(regex);

  if (match && match[2]) {
    return match[2];
  } else {
    throw new Error("Invalid filename format");
  }
}
```

This function takes a string representing the filename as input and returns the three character code. If the filename does not match the expected format, it throws an error.
